{
  "texts": [
    "In their review paper, van Gog and Rummel (2010) synthesized these aspects and provide design guidelines for example processing.",
    "Similarly, Renkl (2002) derived design principles for instructional explanations.",
    "Drawing from the insights of these two review papers, we establish the literature-based design requirements of RELEX:",
    "(L 1) Active processing of examples should be stimulated by emphasizing important aspects of the procedure.",
    "This will help learners understand the underlying structure and transfer that knowledge to a different task (van Gog & Rummel, 2010)."
  ]
}